Partition original dataset

# Set a desired sample size (100,000 observations)
sample_size <- 100000

# Sample the data stratified by BodyGroup
set.seed(123) # For reproducibility
NEISS_sample <- NEISScleaned %>%
  group_by(BodyGroup) %>%
  sample_frac(size = sample_size / nrow(NEISScleaned), replace = FALSE) %>%
  ungroup()

# Verify the sampled dataset
nrow(NEISS_sample)
## [1] 100000
#check Target variable categories
summary(NEISS_sample$Head)
##     0     1 
## 82004 17996
# Partition dataset into 60% of training and 40% of testing
set.seed(123)
train.index=sample(c(1:dim(NEISS_sample)[1]), dim(NEISS_sample)[1]*0.6)
train_data  = NEISS_sample[train.index, ]
test_data = NEISS_sample[-train.index, ]

##Balanced dataset using ROSE

# Balance the dataset using ROSE
set.seed(123)  # For reproducibility
NEISS_balanced <- ROSE(Head ~ Age + Sex + Race + Location + Hispanic + 
                          Fire_Involvement + Alcohol + Drug + Multi_Injuries + 
                          Multi_Products + Year + Month + Day + Weekend + Covid, data = NEISS_sample, seed = 123)$data

# Check the new class distribution
table(NEISS_balanced$Head)

##Adult and Younger Balancing and Partition

# Define a function to sample, balance, and partition datasets
process_age_group <- function(data, age_group_name) {
  set.seed(123)  # For reproducibility

  # Take a 100k sample for the specified age group
  sampled_data <- data[data$AgeGroup2 == age_group_name, ]
  sampled_data <- sampled_data[sample(nrow(sampled_data), 100000, replace = TRUE), ]

  # Balance the dataset using ROSE
  balanced_data <- ROSE(Head ~ Age + Sex + Race + Location + Hispanic + 
                          Fire_Involvement + Alcohol + Drug + Multi_Injuries + 
                          Multi_Products + Year + Month + Day + Weekend + Covid,
                        data = sampled_data, seed = 123)$data

  # Partition the balanced dataset into training (60%) and testing (40%) sets
  set.seed(123)
  train_index <- createDataPartition(balanced_data$Head, p = 0.6, list = FALSE)
  train_data <- balanced_data[train_index, ]
  test_data <- balanced_data[-train_index, ]

  # Return the training and testing datasets
  list(train = train_data, test = test_data)
}

# Apply the function to Younger and Adult datasets
younger_data <- process_age_group(NEISScleaned, "Younger")
adult_data <- process_age_group(NEISScleaned, "Adult")

# Access training and testing datasets for Younger and Adult

test_younger <- younger_data$test

test_adult <- adult_data$test

# Load necessary libraries
library(broom)

# Function to extract coefficients and significance levels
tidy_model <- function(model) {
  summary_df <- tidy(model) %>%
    mutate(significance = case_when(
      p.value < 0.001 ~ "***",
      p.value < 0.01 ~ "**",
      p.value < 0.05 ~ "*",
      p.value < 0.1 ~ ".",
      TRUE ~ ""
    ))
  return(summary_df)
}

# Extract tidy summaries for each model
younger_summary <- tidy_model(log_model_younger) %>% mutate(Model = "Younger")
adult_summary <- tidy_model(log_model_adult) %>% mutate(Model = "Adult")
senior_summary <- tidy_model(log_model_senior) %>% mutate(Model = "Senior")

# Combine the summaries
combined_summary <- bind_rows(younger_summary, adult_summary, senior_summary)

# Reshape for comparison
comparison_table <- combined_summary %>%
  select(term, estimate, significance, Model) %>%
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = Model,
    values_from = c(estimate, significance),
    names_glue = "{Model}_{.value}"
  )

# View the comparison table
print(comparison_table)
